Sentencas: The performance and stability of direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells (DCSOFCs) are severely affected by the electrocatalytic activity of their anode materials.
Titulo: Layered perovskites with exsolved Co-Fe nanoalloy as highly active and stable anodes for direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, a cobalt doped layered perovskite, (PrBa)0.95Fe1.8-xCoxNb0.2O5+delta (PBFCoxN, x = 0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3), is investigated as the anode material for a DCSOFC.
Titulo: Layered perovskites with exsolved Co-Fe nanoalloy as highly active and stable anodes for direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Co3Fe7 alloy particles are exsolved on the perovskite substrate under the reduction of carbon, which improves CO chemisorption and electrochemical oxidation.
Titulo: Layered perovskites with exsolved Co-Fe nanoalloy as highly active and stable anodes for direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This enhances the electrochemical per-formance of the anode.
Titulo: Layered perovskites with exsolved Co-Fe nanoalloy as highly active and stable anodes for direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrolyte-supported cell with a (PrBa)0.95Fe1.6Co0.2Nb0.2O5+delta (PBFCo0.2N) anode achieves a peak power density of 525.6 mW cm-2 at 800 degrees C, fueled by activated carbon.
Titulo: Layered perovskites with exsolved Co-Fe nanoalloy as highly active and stable anodes for direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The performance of this anode material is comparable to or exceeds that of previously reported anodes, indicating that the PBFCo0.2N anode is a promising option for DCSOFCs.
Titulo: Layered perovskites with exsolved Co-Fe nanoalloy as highly active and stable anodes for direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells
